            <div class="Body">
                <p>
                    With cryptocurrency, you can diversify your portfolio 
                    and protect yourself from inflation. Additionally, you 
                    can utilize it as a store of value, which enables you 
                    to profit from an increase in the value of cryptocurrencies 
                    over time. However, there are hazards associated with 
                    investing in cryptocurrencies, so you might need to take 
                    precautions to secure your money from hackers and criminals. 
                    Using a cold storage wallet for cryptocurrency storage that 
                    is disconnected from the internet is one approach to accomplish 
                    this. By doing this, you may be sure that even if someone hacks 
                    into your digital wallet, they won't be able to access all of 
                    your funds unless they also have physical access to them.
                </p>
                <img src="/img/01.png" alt="wallet_collage">
                <p>
                    A Bitcoin wallet with no internet access is referred to as a "cold wallet." 
                    Due to the fact that they cannot be stolen or hacked in public settings, 
                    cold wallets are more secure than hot wallets. They are also more dependable 
                    since only you have access to the private keys, which are stored on a machine 
                    <a href="/phones">separate from your computer</a>. This comes at a price, though, as cold wallets 
                    often cost more than their hot wallet equivalents because they require a 
                    separate device for data storage. Additionally, if you lose possession of your 
                    private key, all of your bitcoins will be irretrievably destroyed!

                </p>
